        <abstract>
            <p>Explains discrepancies in weights and measures caused by changes since 1836 in apothecaries’ measures.</p>
            <p>EC has found that a discrepancy in A. W. von Hofmann’s experiments with iodine solutions resulted from an error in Hofmann’s use of decimals.</p> 
<p>Reports S. P. Woodward’s opinion of the <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>: "a very sad book, it unsettles all one’s religious principles and the worst of it is <hi rend="italic">so much</hi> of it is true".</p> 
        </abstract>
